# Phase 11: Premium Ecosystem & Viral UX

Elevating VibeStream with professional-grade upload controls, transcription intelligence, and an immersive "Shorts" discovery engine.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tier-Based Limits**: Uploading will now be restricted by duration. 
> - **Free Users**: 60 seconds (Shorts only style).
> - **Premium Users**: Up to 30 minutes.
>
> **Transcription Research**: We will implement a "Request Transcript" button on the video settings, which will use an edge function to process audio via OpenAI Whisper.

## Proposed Changes

### Core: Subscription-Aware Uploads
#### [MODIFY] [UploadPage.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/upload/page.tsx)
- Integrate `profile.subscription_tier` check.
- Dynamically set `DURATION_LIMIT` (60s vs 1800s).
- Add client-side validation using [loadedmetadata](file:///C:/GOLive/app/upload/page.tsx#19-27) to block uploads exceeding limits.
- Update UI to show "Premium Limit" status.

---

### UX: Cinematic Video Player
#### [MODIFY] [VideoPlayer.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoPlayer.tsx)
- **Cinematic Mode**: Add a toggle to expand the player to a larger "Theater" view.
- **Improved Scrubber**: Add chapter markers and preview thumbnail support.
- **Glassmorphic Controls**: Refine the control bar with a more premium, translucent look.

---

### Shorts: Vertical Immersion & Discovery
#### [MODIFY] [ShortsPage.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/shorts/page.tsx)
- **Strict Aspect Ratio**: Ensure the player is strictly 9:16 vertical on mobile and centered on desktop.
- **Discovery Reel**: Add a "Trending Shorts" horizontal section on the [Home Page](file:///C:/GOLive/app/page.tsx).
- **Auto-Play/Loop logic**: Refine the intersection observer for smoother scrolling.

---

### Intelligence: Transcription Pipeline
#### [NEW] [transcription.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/transcription.ts)
- Implement a service to extract audio and send it to OpenAI Whisper.
- Store transcripts in a new `transcripts` table.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- Unit test for duration validation logic.
- Verify `subscription_tier` mapping in the upload form.

### Manual Verification
- Attempt to upload a 2-minute video as a Free user (should fail).
- Verify the "Cinematic Mode" expand/collapse animation.
- Confirm Shorts appear in full-screen vertical mode on mobile viewports.
- Click "Share" and verify link persistence.
